		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I also love how Microsoft sets the bottom and right borders of a in-focus window to <span style="color: #40FFFF"><strong>bright fucking cyan</strong></span> in Basic and Classic mode too -- it looks fantastic, especially when using darker colours on your desktop or applications!  And it's <strong>not adjustable either</strong> (don't tell me to go run some of those third-party DWM hackish apps -- I've tried two, they either don't work, or they crash).<br /><br />I've also noticed that dragging/resizing windows is not as smooth in some modes (Aero vs. non-Aero vs. Classic), which is quite amusing given that Windows Vista and 7 are highly DX-driven, thus GPU-driven.<br /><br />What really chaps my ass about every Windows release since XP is that the underlying kernel and many device drivers actually improve -- meaning what goes on under the hood, deep down, is actually good.  It's everything else that turns to shit -- you know, all the stuff you see *constantly* due to the fact that it's a GUI-based OS.

		

